7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
8 Section 1. The elevated portion of Louisiana Highway 433 from Dubee Pena Road
9 to Rivet Drive in the city of Slidell, Louisiana, parish of St. Tammany, shall be known and
10 is hereby designated as the "Emile 'Uncle Tobe' Galatas Memorial Bridge".
11 Section 2. The portion of United States Highway 11 from the Dr. T.J. Smith, Sr.
12 Expressway to Louisiana Highway 41 in the city of Pearl River, Louisiana, parish of St.
13 Tammany, shall be known and is hereby designated the "Captain Steven Gaudet, Jr.
14 Memorial Highway".
15 Section 3. The Department of Transportation and Development or its contractors are
16 hereby directed to erect and maintain appropriate signage reflecting these designations
17 provided local or private monies are received by the department equal to the department's
18 actual cost for material, fabrication, mounting posts, and installation of the signage, not to
19 exceed the sum of seven hundred fifty dollars per sign for the "Emile 'Uncle Tobe' Galatas
